The Chronicle From Golden Sibanda in Cape Town, South Africa
President Mnangagwa has left Cape Town, South Africa, earlier than scheduled following the death of former President Robert Mugabe, Presidential Spokesperson Mr George Charamba has said. The President was in South Africa since Tuesday where he was attending the World Economic Forum on Africa, which ran from Wednesday and ends this afternoon. President Mnangagwa will make a statement on arrival at the Robert Gabriel Mugabe International Airport. More to followâ€¦